I&rsquo;m declaring defeat. Infinite scroll has won.
There is an endless supply of interesting things to consume online, and there are teams and teams of very smart people working very hard to get me to keep watching. One more video means one more metric counter incrementing, one more engagement click, one more step towards growth, ad revenue, product success&hellip;
The danger for me is that I fall in. It&rsquo;s so easy to open an app in an automatic movement of muscle memory, filling up an empty moment without conscious thought.

&ldquo;I&rsquo;m going to be 29 anyways, so I might as well be 29 with a Master&rsquo;s.&rdquo;
— me 5 years ago debating whether I should take classes
 On June 5, 2017, I started taking classes at Tufts University while working full time. On January 4, 2022, I submitted the final draft of my Master&rsquo;s thesis. Much like my past self had hoped, I&rsquo;ve made it 4 years in the future, and I&rsquo;m done with my Master&rsquo;s program.
